order.packing

Interface IContainer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IBox

    public interface IContainer
extends IBox

    Escola Superior de Tecnologia e Gestão (ESTG)
    Politécnico do Porto (PP)
    Licenciatura em Engenharia Informática (LEI)
    Licenciatura em Segurança Informática em Redes de Computadores (LSIRC)
    Paradigmas de Programação (PP)
    2019 / 2020

    Contract representing the Container behaviour as IBox specialization. This class stores an immutable collection of packed items

    • Method Detail

      • addItem

        boolean addItem(IItem item,
                IPosition position,
                Color color)
         throws ContainerException
        Adds a new IItemPacked to the container considering the given item, position and color
        Parameters:
        item - item to be added
        position - position in which the item will be placed
        color - color used for the item
        Returns:
        1. true if the item is inserted in the container. When the item is inserted, the volume should be updated. If there isn't enough space in the collection, the collection should be adjusted to store more items
        2. false if the item already exists in the container
        Throws:
        ContainerException - if:
        1. any parameter is null
        2. the container is closed

      • removeItem

        boolean removeItem(IItem item)
            throws ContainerException
        Removes an item from the container
        Parameters:
        item - item to be added
        Returns:
        1. true if the item is removed in the container. When the item is removed, the volume should be updated.
        2. false if the item doesn't exists in the container
        Throws:
        ContainerException - if:
        1. the parameter is null
        2. the container is closed

      • validate

        void validate()
       throws ContainerException,
              PositionException
        Validates the container structure considering:
        1. if the volume if lesser or equal to the current volume
        2. if all items are inside the container
        3. if non of the items inside the container are overlapping
        Throws:
        ContainerException - if the volume greater than the current volume
        PositionException - if some item is outside (or is overflowing) the container or if some item is overlapping with other item

      • close

        void close()
    throws ContainerException,
           PositionException
        Close the container. Before closing the container, a validation procedure is performed.
        Throws:
        ContainerException - if the volume greater than the current volume
        PositionException - if some item is outside (or is overflowing) the container or if some item is overlapping with other item
